J-K: 7 armymen injured after terrorists attack patrolling party in Shopian district J-K: 7 armymen injured after terrorists attack patrolling party in Shopian district Seven Army personnel are injured after terrorists attacked a patrolling party in Shopian district, Jammu and Kashmir. By: Express Web Desk | New Delhi | Updated: February 23, 2017 7:28 am 
Seven Army personnel have been injured after a patrolling party in Shopian district of Jammu and Kashmir was attacked by terrorists on Thursday. Further details are awaited. © The Indian Express Online Media Pvt Ltd
